The presidency have announced that President Muhammadu Buhari has signed the bill that repeals the prison act and changes the Nigeria Prisons Service to Nigeria Correctional Service. This was announced Wednesday on Twitter as shown below: President @MBuhari has given assent to the Nigerian Correctional Service Bill, 2019. The new Act repeals the Prisons Act and changes the name of the Nigerian Prisons Service to the Nigerian Correctional Service.